settings.title: Leakproof Underwear
settings.copy: Saalt Wear absorbs periods, bladder leaks, and more. Live life leak-free with the thinnest and driest leakproof and period underwear.

settings.title: Cups & Discs
settings.copy: Upgrade your period with Saalt reusable menstrual cups and discs. Easy to use and comfortable. Live free of the tampon aisle—forever. Wear up to 12 hours to swim, run, bike, hike, or fly to Bora Bora.

settings.title: Bundles
settings.copy: Save up to 20% and skip the guesswork with bundles custom-designed by our Saalt Coaches for all your leak needs.

settings.title: Teen
settings.copy:
Peace out, pads.
Modern teens are upgrading to comfortable and sustainable period care. Choose from reusable period cups made by teens for teens, and leakproof period underwear that ranges from size XXS and up.

settings.title: Extras
settings.copy: All the extras that make it easy to care for your underwear, cups, and discs.

settings.text_content: “I started Saalt to help my aunt in Venezuela. Now tens of thousands of people have a better period every month in 50 countries across the world.”

settings.title: Ta-ta tampon tax. We're taking a stand.

settings.text_content: Live in one of the 21 states that still charges sales tax on period products? Saalt has joined a coalition of 8 period brands taking a stand. Learn how you can get your tax reimbursed via Venmo.

settings.title: Meet Saalt Wear. The thinnest, driest, and most comfortable leakproof period underwear.

settings.text_content: Holds up to 6+ pads worth of periods, bladder leaks, sweat, and wetness while keeping you (magically) dry.

settings.quote: Game changing!!This is the first cup I've ever used and I LOVE it! Literally cannot feel it at all when inserted. And the underwear is so comfortable, much more so than disposable pads. I was skeptical but they are some sort of sorcery because they stay dry! I'm telling anyone who will listen to give these products a try.
settings.author: Kelsey R.

settings.quote: Love the style and softness. Probably least bulky period panties for the amount of fluids it can hold. Tried {other brands}. Saalt is the most luxurious and best fitting out of all of them. Some have weird bulk at the crotch or too stiff or wide down there.
settings.author: Kimberly P.

settings.quote: Never going back to tampons! This is my first ever cup I’ve bought. So easy to use and I can’t even tell that it’s there. I ordered a size regular and it was the perfect fit for me. It makes it easier for me to use a cup because I have a heavy flow and I know that I don’t have to change my tampon every hour. I love this product. I’m so glad that I switched to a cup.
settings.author: Courtney M.

settings.quote: So soft and comfy. I like this fabric WAY MORE than my Thinx. Thinner and fit is just overall better. Definitely happy I switched over to Saalt.
